        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 11:17PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 1117 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Winston-Salem, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winston-Salem, Kernersville, Clemmons, Bermuda Run, Lewisville,
Summerfield, Stokesdale, Walkertown, Haw River State Park, and
Pfafftown.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
